This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-categories of cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper discusses the use of FPGAs as a CNN accelerator, which falls under the category of hardware architecture. The focus of the paper is on image classification, which is a common task in computer vision and pattern recognition. The paper also discusses the use of quantization in neural networks, which is a topic in machine learning. Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of a custom hardware-friendly approach, which falls under the category of systems and control, and the use of a single scale integer representation, which is a topic in neural and evolutionary computing.
